Git Commands Cheat Sheet

Basic Commands

git init  : Initialize a new Git repository
git clone <repo_url>	: Clone an existing repository
git status   : Show status of working directory
git add <file>	: Stage file(s) for commit
git add .  : 	Stage all changes
git commit -m "message"	 :  Commit staged changes with a message
git commit -am "message"	: Stage tracked files and commit in one step
git diff	: Show changes not staged for commit
git diff --staged	: Show staged changes
git log	: Show commit history
git log --oneline --graph --all	 : Visual commit history

Branching Commands
git branch : List all branches
git branch <branch_name>	: Create a new branch
git checkout <branch_name>	: Switch to branch
git switch <branch_name>	: Alternative to checkout
git checkout -b <branch_name>	: Create & switch to branch
git switch -c <branch_name>	: Alternative for creating & switching
git branch -d <branch_name>	: Delete a local branch
git branch -D <branch_name>	 : Force delete branch
git branch -r	  :  List remote branches
git branch -a	:  List local + remote branches

Merging Commands

git merge <branch>	: Merge a branch into current branch
git merge --no-ff <branch>	: Merge with a merge commit (no fast-forward)
git rebase <branch>	:  Reapply commits on top of another branch
git rebase -i <commit>	: Interactive rebase to edit commits
git mergetool	:  Open GUI merge tool to resolve conflicts

Undoing / Reset Commands

git reset <file>	:  Unstage file
git reset --soft <commit>	: Move HEAD to commit, keep changes staged
git reset --mixed <commit> : Move HEAD to commit, keep changes unstaged
git reset --hard <commit> : 	Move HEAD to commit, discard changes
git checkout -- <file>	: Discard changes in working directory
git revert <commit>	: Revert a commit by creating a new commit

Remote Commands

git remote -v	:  List remote repositories
git remote add <name> <url>	:  Add a remote repository
git fetch <remote>	:  Fetch changes from remote without merging
git pull	:  Fetch + merge from remote
git pull --rebase	:  Fetch + rebase from remote
git push <remote> <branch>	:  Push local branch to remote
git push -u <remote> <branch>	:  Push & set upstream tracking
git push --force	:  Force push changes (dangerous!)
git push --all	:  Push all branches
git push --tags	:  Push all tags

Tagging Commands

git tag	:  List all tags
git tag <tag_name> :  Create a lightweight tag
git tag -a <tag_name> -m "message"	: Create annotated tag
git show <tag_name>	:  tag info
git push <remote> <tag_name> : Push a specific tag
git push --tags	:  Push all tags

Stashing Commands

git stash	: Stash changes
git stash list	: Show stash list
git stash apply	: Apply latest stash
git stash apply stash@{n}	: Apply specific stash
git stash pop	: Apply + drop stash
git stash drop stash@{n}	: Delete a specific stash
git stash clear	:  Delete all stashes

Viewing History / Logs

git log	:  Show commit history
git log --oneline :  Condensed commit history
git log --graph --decorate --all :  Visual graph
git show <commit>	:  Show commit details
git blame <file>: Show last change for each line
git reflog	:  Show history of HEAD changes

Advanced / Useful Commands

git cherry-pick <commit>	:  Apply a commit from another branch
git bisect start	: Start bisect to find bug commit
git bisect good/bad	: Mark commits during bisect
git clean -f	:  Remove untracked files
git clean -fd	: Remove untracked files & directories
git rm <file> :	Delete file from repo & working dir
git mv <old> <new>	: Rename file in repo
git config --global user.name "Name"	:  Set Git username
git config --global user.email "email"	:  Set Git email
git config --list	:  Show Git config
git shortlog	:  Summarize commits by author
